1. *Polazi* mi za rukom da završim sve zadatke na vreme. (I manage to finish all tasks on time.)
2. On *polazi* u školu u 7 ujutru. (He leaves for school at 7 in the morning.)
3. Kada *polaziš* na put, obavezno ponesi sve potrebne stvari. (When you set off on a trip, be sure to bring all the necessary things.)
4. Moja sestra *polazi* sutra za Beograd. (My sister is leaving for Belgrade tomorrow.)
5. Da li ti *polazi* za rukom da skuvaš dobru kafu? (Are you able to make good coffee?)
6. *Polazeći* od početka godine, primetila sam veliki napredak u svom radu. (Starting from the beginning of the year, I noticed great progress in my work.)
7. Oni su *polazili* u istu školu. (They went to the same school.)
8. Kad *polaze* autobusi za Novi Sad? (When do buses leave for Novi Sad?)
9. Koliko vremena ti *polazi* za Beograd? (How much time do you need to get to Belgrade?)
10. *Polazeći* od ove pretpostavke, lako se može doći do pogrešnih zaključaka. (Starting from this assumption, one can easily come to wrong conclusions.)